publicationStmt.p: The WordHoard Shakespeare is a joint project of the Perseus Project at Tufts University, The Northwestern University Library, and Northwestern University Academic Technologies. It is derived from The Globe Shakespeare , the one-volume version of the Cambridge Shakespeare , edited by W. G. Clark, J. Glover, and W. A. Wright (1891-3). The Internet Shakespeare editions of the quartos and folios have been consulted to create a modern text that observes as closely as possible the morphological and prosodic practices of the earliest editions. Spellings, especially of contracted and hyphenated forms, have been standardized across the corpus. The text has been fully lemmatized and morphosyntactically tagged.

sourceDesc.p: The Wordhoard Shakespeare is derived from, but not identical with, The Globe Shakespeare , the one-volume version of the Cambridge Shakespeare (1891-3) edited by W. G. Clark, J. Glover, and W. A. Wright.

castItem.roleDesc: a noble Moor in the service of the Venetian state
Othello's predecessor in the government of Cyprus
daughter to Brabantio and wife to Othello

l.stage: BRABANTIO appears above, at a window.
Enter, below, BRABANTIO, and Servants with torches.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 2
div.stage: Enter OTHELLO, IAGO, and Attendants with torches.

l.stage: Enter CASSIO, and certain Officers with torches.
Enter BRABANTIO, RODERIGO, and Officers with torches and weapons.

div.head: Act 1, Scene 3
div.stage: A council-chamber. The DUKE and Senators sitting at a table; Officers attending.

l.stage: Enter BRABANTIO, OTHELLO, IAGO, RODERIGO, and Officers.

div.head: Act 2, Scene 1
div.stage: A Sea-port in Cyprus. An open place near the quay.

l.stage: A cry within “A sail, a sail, a sail!”
Enter DESDEMONA, EMILIA, IAGO, RODERIGO, and Attendants.
Within 'A sail, a sail!” Guns heard.

div.head: Act 2, Scene 2
div.stage: Enter a Herald with a proclamation; People following.

div.head: Act 2, Scene 3
div.stage: Enter OTHELLO, DESDEMONA, CASSIO, and Attendants.

sp.speaker: Iago
sp.stage: Re-enter CASSIO; with him MONTANO and Gentlemen; Servants following with wine.

l.stage: To Montano, who is led off.
Exeunt all but Iago and Cassio.
He puts the handkerchief from him; and it drops.

div.head: Act 4, Scene 3
div.stage: Enter OTHELLO, LODOVICO, DESDEMONA, EMILIA, and Attendants.

l.stage: Iago from behind wounds Cassio in the leg, and exit.
Cassio and Roderigo are borne off.

div.head: Act 5, Scene 2
div.stage: A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.

l.stage: Enter MONTANO, GRATIANO, IAGO, and others.
He runs at Iago: Iago, from behind, stabs Emilia, and exit.

sp.speaker: Othello
sp.stage: Enter LODOVICO, MONTANO, CASSIO carried in a chair, and Officers with IAGO, prisoner.

l.stage: Falls on the bed, and dies.
